special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: BATMAN
special_powers.description: Give Bruce Wayne a power action and replace this character with a BB #016 Batman on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement Batman. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement Batman is considered to be 48 points for all game effects.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: SUPERMAN
special_powers.description: Give Clark Kent a power action and replace this character with a BB #017 Superman on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement Superman. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement Superman is considered to be 48 points for all game effects.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: WONDER WOMAN
special_powers.description: Give Diana Prince a power action and replace this character with a BB #018 Wonder Woman on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement Wonder Woman. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement Wonder Woman is considered to be 32 points for all game effects.

special_powers.name: MINION: TRAINING FROM THE ELITE
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the League of Assassins keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares; League Assassin can use Exploit Weakness.

special_powers.name: MINION: SISTERS UNITED
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the Amazon keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares, Amazon can use Willpower and modifies her attack value by +1.

special_powers.name: BATTLEFIELD PROMOTION
special_powers.description: When Checkmate Pawn (White) KOs or critical hits a character, after the action is resolved but before pushing damage is applied you may replace this character with Brave and the Bold #007 Checkmate Knight (White) and victory points are not awarded for this character.

special_powers.name: MINION: HORDES OF APOKOLIPS
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the Apokolips keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares, Parademon Grunt modifies its attack and speed values by +1.

special_powers.name: BIG TARGET OR LITTLE TARGET
special_powers.description: (non-optional) The Atom and Hawkman possess Toughness. Before making an attack which would affect The Atom and Hawkman, the attacking player chooses Super Senses or Invulnerability. The Atom and Hawkman use the chosen power instead of Toughness for that attack.

special_powers.name: ALTER EGO: ETRIGAN
special_powers.description: Give this character a power action and replace this character with a BB #039 Etrigan on its orange starting line. Existing action tokens from this character, as well as action tokens and pushing damage for this action are applied to the replacement Etrigan. If replaced, no victory points are awarded for this character and the replacement Etrigan is considered to be 44 points for all game effects.

special_powers.name: VITAL STRIKE
special_powers.description: If League Elite's damage value is 5 or more when resolving the attack, deal 1 penetrating damage to the target after resolving the initial attack.

special_powers.name: BATTLEFIELD PROMOTION
special_powers.description: When Checkmate Pawn (Black) KOs or critical hits a character, after the action is resolved but before pushing damage is applied you may replace this character with BB #014 Checkmate Knight (Black) on its starting click. If replaced, existing action tokens from this character are applied to the replacement Checkmate Knight (Black) and victory points are not awarded for this character.

special_powers.name: DARKSEID'S MOTIVATIONAL TECHNIQUES
special_powers.description: (non-optional) When an adjacent friendly character makes an attack, modify that character's damage value by +1 for that attack. If the attack roll misses all targets, deal the attacking character 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: LASSO PUNCH
special_powers.description: Give Wonder Woman a power action. Choose a target non-adjacent opposing character within 2 squares of Wonder Woman to whom she has a clear line of fire. Place that character in a square of clear terrain adjacent to its current square and Wonder Woman and then she makes a close combat attack against the target character as a free action.

special_powers.name: UNDERCOVER
special_powers.description: Wild cards cannot copy team abilities from Talia.

special_powers.name: SON OF THE BAT
special_powers.description: Damian Wayne can use Exploit Weakness and Outwit.

special_powers.name: THE MIGHTY MOLE
special_powers.description: Cave Carson can use Phasing/Teleport. When he does, he can use the Carry ability, and must place debris tokens into the squares where he begins and ends his movement. Cave Carson ignores the effects of debris tokens on movement.

special_powers.name: CAVE-IN
special_powers.description: When Cave Carson is grounded, he can use Quake, but only if he is adjacent to elevated terrain or he occupies or is adjacent to a square containing a debris token.

special_powers.name: SPEEDFORCE MENTOR
special_powers.description: Max Mercury can use Perplex, but can only use it to modify another character's speed value by +3.

special_powers.name: TRAIT
special_powers.description: Mikron O'Jeneus can't carry other characters.

special_powers.name: UNBELIEVABLE WEAPONRY
special_powers.description: Once per game (but not during another action) when Mikron O'Jeneus is adjacent to a non-held object, as a free action remove that object from the game and choose a standard attack power. Mikron O'Jeneus and up to two friendly characters adjacent to Mikron O'Jeneus can use that power until the beginning of your next turn (even if they are no longer adjacent to Mikron O'Jeneus).

special_powers.name: A LESSON LEARNED
special_powers.description: Goodness and Mercy can use Exploit Weakness and Willpower.

special_powers.name: NO PLACE FOR MERCY
special_powers.description: (non-optional) Goodness and Mercy have the fist attack symbol.

special_powers.name: ASSASSINATION AS ART FORM
special_powers.description: Once per turn if an opposing character is KO'd by another friendly character that shares a keyword with The Sensei, that action does not count against your action total for the turn and remove one action token from The Sensei.

special_powers.name: FAULT LINE
special_powers.description: Give The Sensei a power action and choose the row or column on the map occupied by The Sensei. Destroy all blocking terrain in that row or column as well as any walls that border 2 squares of that row or column. Deal 1 unavoidable damage to The Sensei and 1 damage to all characters that can't use the Flight ability occupying that row or column. Place debris markers as appropriate.

special_powers.name: THE AMAZON GENERAL
special_powers.description: Phillipus can use Probability Control, but can only affect attack rolls. If neither that attacking nor any defending characters for a chosen attack roll possess the Amazon keyword, deal Phillipus 1 unavoidable damage after the attack is resolved.

special_powers.name: SUPERIOR STRATEGY
special_powers.description: Phillipus can use Outwit but can only counter defense powers.

special_powers.name: IMPROVISE
special_powers.description: Whenever Mademoiselle Marie KOs an opposing character, put an improvise token on her character card if she doesn't have one already. If an attack roll made by her misses, but is not a critical miss, you may remove an improvise token to automatically hit instead.

special_powers.name: MOTHERBOX DETONATION
special_powers.description: The Parademon can use Pulse Wave as if he had a range value of 10. After that action is resolved, deal him 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: SHRINK RAY
special_powers.description: Brainiac can use Incapacitate. If his attack using Incapacitate succeeds, the targeted character also modifies their speed and damage values by -2 and their defense values by +2 until the beginning of your next turn.

special_powers.name: SUPERMAN'S BANE
special_powers.description: (non-optional) Characters within 8 squares of Kryptonite Man that possess the Superman Ally team ability or are named "Superman" have Earthbound/Neutralized and damage dealt to them may not be reduced below 1. When these characters are given a non-free action, modify their speed values by -3 for that action.

special_powers.name: KRYTONITE CORE
special_powers.description: Metallo can use Poison and Super Strength.

special_powers.name: MALLEABILITY
special_powers.description: Metallo can use Blades/Claws/Fangs, Plasticity, and Shape Change.

special_powers.name: LAZARUS PIT
special_powers.description: When Ra's al Ghul is KOd, remove him from the map and place him on his character card. At the beginning of your turn, you may heal Ra's al Ghul of 1 damage. After his starting click is revealed, you may place him in any starting area as a free action during your turn. Opponents receive victory points each time Ra's al Ghul is KOd.

special_powers.name: TRAIT
special_powers.description: Power Girl can use Super Strength.

special_powers.name: EYES UP HERE, SOLDIER
special_powers.description: Power Girl can use Exploit Weakness, but cannot use it on a character that can use Willpower or Indomitable or a character that possesses the Robot keyword.

special_powers.name: TRAIT
special_powers.description: Martian Manhunter can use Shape Change and Phasing/Teleport.

special_powers.name: TELEPATHIC INVISIBILITY
special_powers.description: Once at the beginning of your turn, you may choose close combat attack or ranged combat attack. Martian Manhunter modifies his defense by +3 against the chosen type of attack until the beginning of your next turn.

special_powers.name: AGED OR DE-AGED
special_powers.description: Extant can use Incapacitate, but his damage value becomes 1 instead of 0 until the action is resolved.

special_powers.name: TIME AND SPACE
special_powers.description: Extant can use Super Senses and Energy Shield/Deflection.

special_powers.name: MULTI-DIMENSIONAL ATTACK
special_powers.description: When a character takes damage from Extant's attack, all other characters on the map with the exact same name take an equal amount of damage.

special_powers.name: SLOW DOWN
special_powers.description: Opposing characters that are given a non-free action within 6 squares of Inertia replace their speed values with half their unmodified speed value for that action.

special_powers.name: AND HELLFIRE BURN
special_powers.description: Etrigan can use Energy Explosion. When Etrigan uses Energy Explosion, damage dealt is penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: OF RHYME OR REASON
special_powers.description: Etrigan can use Perplex and Probability Control.

special_powers.name: SUMMON THE SKULLSHIP
special_powers.description: Lex Luthor and Brainiac has [transporter flight speed symbol symbol] and can carry up to 12 adjacent friendly characters.

special_powers.name: THE SMARTEST GUYS IN THE ROOM
special_powers.description: Lex Luthor and Brainiac can use Outwit. Lex Luthor and Brainiac's Superman Enemy team ability ignores this Outwit Power.

special_powers.name: SEDUCTRESS
special_powers.description: Talia al Ghul can use Mind Control. When targeting an opposing character possessing the Batman Ally team ability or named "Batman", she modifies her attack value by +2 and heals 1 damage instead of taking any damage from Mind Control.

special_powers.name: YOU CAN'T HURT THE THING YOU LOVE
special_powers.description: Talia al Ghul can use Shape Change and Perplex. When using Perplex, she can only target herself or opposing characters.

special_powers.name: LEVERAGE
special_powers.description: Robin can use Leap/Climb. Whenever Robin makes a close combat attack against a single opposing character that possesses an unmodified damage value of 3 or more, after the attack is resolved, put the target in any unoccupied square adjacent to Robin.

special_powers.name: TIMELINE PUSH
special_powers.description: Kid Zoom can use Incapacitate. He can use it normally, or he can use its close combat attack as a free action instead of a close combat attack while using Hypersonic Speed.

special_powers.name: STOP!
special_powers.description: (non-optional) Other characters can't use Hypersonic Speed.

special_powers.name: THE SLOW LIGHTNING
special_powers.description: Black Flash can use Phasing/Teleport. Black Flash modifies his attack value by +2 if the target of his attack has a speed value greater than or equal to Black Flash.

special_powers.name: DEATH COMES SWIFTLY
special_powers.description: Black Flash can use Poison. When Poison is used, adjacent opposing characters that can use Hypersonic Speed are dealt 2 damage instead.

special_powers.name: CONFINED TO THE ROCK
special_powers.description: (non-optional) The Wizard Shazam! gains Earthbound/Neutralized, and can't be carried or the target of the Telekinesis power option 1 or 2.

special_powers.name: VIEW FROM ABOVE
special_powers.description: The Wizard Shazam! can use Enhancement and Probability Control. When he uses Probability Control, he may target a character anywhere on the map.

special_powers.name: TRAIT
special_powers.description: Batman and Green Arrow possess the Sharpshooter ability.

special_powers.name: FROM THE DARK ALLEYS
special_powers.description: Batman and Green Arrow can use Stealth, and ignore other characters' Stealth.

special_powers.name: NO GUNS...UTILITY BELTS AND TRICK ARROWS
special_powers.description: Batman and Green Arrow can use Incapacitate. If that attack succeeds against any target, they can use Smoke Cloud as a free action for each success.

special_powers.name: INTO THE SPEED FORCE
special_powers.description: Give The Flashes a power action. Remove all objects and up to 300 points of other characters from the map. Place all removed objects back on the map and then place all removed characters on the map. All placements must be legal. Deal The Flashes 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: HELP FROM THE FUTURE
special_powers.description: The Flashes can use Probability Control.

special_powers.name: AROUND THE WORLD IN 80 MICROSECONDS
special_powers.description: The Flashes can use Flurry. Before each attack while using Flurry, you may place The Flashes adjacent to any opposing character on the map if their entire base is adjacent to the target character and in clear terrain.

special_powers.name: WHO'S CARRYING WHO NOW?
special_powers.description: The Flash and Green Lantern can use Hypersonic Speed and have the boot movement symbol.

special_powers.name: THE BRAVE AND THE BOLD
special_powers.description: Give The Flash and Green Lantern a power action. They can use Telekinesis twice as a free action.

special_powers.name: TWO-MAN JUSTICE LEAGUE
special_powers.description: Once during your turn, as a free action you may choose a standard damage power that no other character on your force currently possesses or can use. The Flash and Green Lantern can use that power until the beginning of your next turn.

special_powers.name: KEEPING PACE
special_powers.description: Before any non-free action, you may replace Superman and The Flash's speed value with the highest unmodified speed value among characters on the map until that action is resolved. Use this ability only if you haven't chosen Superman or the Flash.

special_powers.name: SPEED POWER
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Hypersonic Speed, has the boot speed symbol, and modifies his speed values by +2. OR Superman can use Charge, and has the wing speed symbol.

special_powers.name: AND THE WINNER IS...
special_powers.description: (non-optional) Once per game, when this power is first revealed, you must choose Superman or The Flash. For all other Special Powers for this character, only use the powers of the chosen character this game. This character has the fist attack symbol. This power can't be countered or ignored.

special_powers.name: DEFENSE POWER
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Super Senses. OR Superman can use Invulnerability.

special_powers.name: DAMAGE POWER
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Outwit. OR Superman can use Enhancement and modifies his damage value by +2.

special_powers.name: FREEZE'R BURN
special_powers.description: Fire and Ice can use Barrier, Poison, and Toughness. When this figure uses Poison, it may treat all opposing figures which ended the previous turn adjacent to one of Fire and Ice's blocking terrain markers as adjacent.

special_powers.name: MUST HELP...MY SIDEKICK...THE JUNKIE!
special_powers.description: Green Lantern and Green Arrow ignore damage dealt by characters using Poison. Friendly characters do not take pushing damage if they can use Poison and are adjacent to Green Lantern and Green Arrow when the pushing damage is applied.

special_powers.name: SAVE MORE THAN THE BLUE, ORANGE, AND PURPLE SKINS
special_powers.description: Whenever Green Lantern and Green Arrow use the Duo Attack ability for ranged attacks, they can target more than one target with each attack and ignore any damage modifiers from the Duo Attack ability.

special_powers.name: HELPING THE UNDERPRIVILEGED
special_powers.description: Adjacent friendly characters of 30 points or less modify their attack values by +1.

special_powers.name: YES, I GUESS I'LL CARRY YOU
special_powers.description: Blue Beetle and Booster Gold can't carry other character. When they use the Duo Attack ability, they ignore any damage modifiers from the Duo Attack ability.

special_powers.name: SUPER BUDDIES FOREVER
special_powers.description: Friendly adjacent characters modify their attack value by +1 if they either share a keyword with Blue Beetle and Booster Gold or can use the Duo attack ability.

special_powers.name: MY GADGET OR YOURS?
special_powers.description: Blue Beetle and Booster Gold can use Energy Shield/Deflection and Toughness.

special_powers.name: TOXIC IMMUNITY SERUM
special_powers.description: Harley Quinn and Poison Ivy and friendly characters within 6 squares ignore damage dealt by Poison.

special_powers.name: RECLAIMING THE LAND FOR NATURE
special_powers.description: Harley Quinn and Poison Ivy can use Poison and Smoke Cloud. When hindering terrain markers placed by Harley Quinn and Poison Ivy are removed at the beginning of your turn, you may destroy one wall or square of blocking terrain adjacent to at least one of the markers.

special_powers.name: LADIES' CHOICE
special_powers.description: Harley Quinn and Poison Ivy can use Toughness and Combat Reflexes.

special_powers.name: MAYHEM - HARLEY STYLE
special_powers.description: Harley Quinn and Poison Ivy can use Outwit, but after targeting an opposing character, roll a d6. On a result of 1, this power has no effect. On a result of 2-3, counter one power as normal. On a result of 4-6, counter two powers instead.

special_powers.name: NO CHAINS CAN HOLD ME
special_powers.description: Mister Miracle and Oberon can use Charge and Leap/Climb. When they use Charge, they can ignore the effects of hindering terrain and characters on movement and automatically breaks away.

special_powers.name: PRISON BREAK!
special_powers.description: Friendly characters within 6 squares ignore opponent's Plasticity and succeed on break away results of 2-6.

special_powers.name: YOUR HEAD IS MY JUMPING OFF POINT
special_powers.description: Friendly adjacent characters can use Telekinesis option 2 but only targeting this character.

special_powers.name: RELUCTANT TEAM-UP
special_powers.description: When you build your force, choose a 140 or 280 point cost. In both cases, each time you reveal your force at the beginning of a game choose the light green starting line (Shazam!) or the dark green starting line (Black Adam). If you chose 140 points, this character is KO'd when the first red KO line is crossed. If you chose 280 points, this character is KO'd when the second red KO line is crossed.

special_powers.name: FURY ENOUGH TO DESTROY COUNTRIES
special_powers.description: Black Adam can use Hypersonic Speed. If he can also use Close Combat Expert or Exploit Weakness, he can use that power as a free action instead of a close combat attack while using Hypersonic Speed.

special_powers.name: CALL DOWN THE LIGHTNING
special_powers.description: Shazam can use Energy Explosion as if he had a range of 6. Each character successfully hit is dealt damage equal to twice the number of times it was hit by this attack instead of once.

special_powers.name: DRAIN THE SPECTRUM
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, choose red, orange, yellow, green, light blue, or purple. This turn, opposing characters within 8 squares of Black Hand displaying a power of the chosen color modify their defense values by -2.

special_powers.name: AVATAR OF THE BLACK
special_powers.description: Black Hand can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast. Whenever an opposing character is KO'd within 4 squares of Black Hand, you may heal 1 damage on any one friendly character to whom Black Hand can draw a line of fire.

special_powers.name: POWER LEVELS RISING
special_powers.description: Whenever an opposing character is KO'd within 4 squares of Martian Manhunter, you may heal Martian Manhunter of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: DECAYING EMBRACE
special_powers.description: Martian Manhunter can use Plasticity and Phasing/Teleport. Whenever an adjacent opposing character fails a break away roll, deal that character 1 damage after the action is resolved.

special_powers.name: POWER LEVELS RISING
special_powers.description: Whenever an opposing character is KO'd within 4 squares of Kal-L, you may heal Kal-L of 1 damage.

special_powers.name: FENDING OFF TWO SUPERMEN
special_powers.description: Kal-L can use Flurry. For each character successfully hit while using Flurry, after the close combat action is resolved Kal-L can use Force Blast as free action targeting that character.

special_powers.name: TERROR OF A DARK GOD
special_powers.description: Nekron can use Pulse Wave as if he had a range of 8. After the Pulse Wave action is resolved, each character hit is knocked back 2 squares. This knock back can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: THE BLACKEST NIGHT
special_powers.description: Whenever an opposing character is KO'd during your turn within 8 squares of Nekron, they are considered KO'd, but do not remove them from the map and heal them of 1 damage. After all current actions have resolved, that character becomes friendly to your force and you may immediately asign them one action as a free action. After this action is resolved, remove that character from the map.

special_powers.name: I ALREADY STOLE THE REAL ONE
special_powers.description: Once at the beginning of the game, after objects are placed, you may remove an object placed by an opponent from the map and place a standard light object in the same square.

special_powers.name: DOUBLE POUNCE
special_powers.description: Batman and Catwoman can use Leap/Climb. When Batman and Catwoman are given a move action, after the movement is complete Batman and Catwoman may use the Duo Attack ability as a free action.

special_powers.name: SUMMON THE BAT OR SET THE TRAP
special_powers.description: Give Batman and Catwoman a power action and choose target character within 6 squares who possesses the Batman Ally or the Batman Enemy Team ability (line of fire is not required). Place the target character in an unoccupied square adjacent to Batman and Catwoman. If the target is friendly, it can't be given an action until your next turn.

special_powers.name: ROMANTIC TENSION
special_powers.description: Batman and Catwoman can use Combat Reflexes and Willpower.

special_powers.name: INVESTIGATIVE REPORTING
special_powers.description: Give Clark a power action. Choose an opposing character within 6 squares. That character can't use Stealth this turn and their combat values cannot be modified this turn.
Combat values cannot be replaced by the combat values of other characters.

special_powers.name: Prerequisites
special_powers.description: Duo

Choose a character. When using the Duo Attack ability, if this character KO's an opposing character with the first attack, you may choose to not give this character a free action for the second attack. Instead, do not give this character an action token for the action, though the action still counts towards your available actions.

special_powers.name: Prerequisites
special_powers.description: Duo

Choose a character. If this character possesses Blades/Claws/Fangs, Energy Explosion, Pulse Wave, Quake, Incapacitate, Penetrating/Psychic Blast or Telekinesis and uses it as an attack, after actions resolve, it may make a close or ranged combat attack as a free action, but modifies its attack and damage values by -1 for that attack.

Choose a character. Whenever this character attacks an opposing character possessing a Special Power, if this character currently possesses no Special Power or Traits, modify this character's attack value by +1.

special_powers.name: Prerequisites
special_powers.description: Energy Explosion
Choose a character. Whenever a total of 2 or more damage is taken by opposing characters while this character is using Energy Explosion, heal this character of 1 damage after actions resolve.
Characters within 4 squares of this object that can use Battle Fury modify their damage value by +1.
When a character uses Poison within 4 squares of this object, that character is considered to be adjacent to opposing characters up to two squares away to which is has a clear line of fire.
Characters within 4 squares of this object that can use Exploit Weakness or Penetrating/Psychic Blast modify their attack value by +1.
Characters within 4 squares of this object that can use Indomitable or Willpower modify their defense values by +3 when they are the target of an attack using Incapacitate or Mind Control.

Characters within 4 squares of this object that can use Barrier or Telekinesis modify their range values by +2 and can use Telekinesis for 10 squares instead of 8 (for all limitations of Telekinesis) if they can already use Telekinesis.
Characters within 4 squares of this object that can use Support or Regeneration only subtract 1 from their die roll instead of 2 when using those powers.

Characters within 4 squares of this object that can use Mind Control modify their range value for that attack by +2 (figures with a range of 0 replace their range with 6 instead of 4 for that attack), and if that attack is successful, each character successfully hit modifies its damage value by +1 until its free action granted by Mind Control is resolved.
During your turn, whenever an opposing character within 4 squares of this object is KOd, you may heal 1 damage on a single friendly character within 4 squares of this object.

special_powers.name: Open Graves
special_powers.description: Orange squares are hindering terrain for movement purposes and clear terrain for line of fire purposes. Any line of fire drawn to a character occupying an orange square is blocked.
